Basics of debugging

Debugger?
=========
- Helps you execute your program line by line. Inspect the variable.
   -- You can stop the program anywhere you want
- C: gdb
- python : pdb
- JavaScript: browser based debugger / other
Anyone can make a debugger. Just some standard ones
are named here.


- VScode/CodeBlocks: You can run debugger in them.

gdb
===
-g flag?
--------
- Adds debug symbol
-O0 flag?
---------
- No optimization


....... Oversimplified Description......
================commands================
- l : list // shows the source
- n : Execute next one line
- r: run: runs the program
- start: runs the program and stops at main
- p: to see a value of a variable
- b: breakpoint  usage: b function_name/// b lineNumber
- d: delete breakpoint
- c: continue
- s: step
- f: finish (get out of that function)


ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE FOR YOUR ACCOUNT MUST BE SET PROPERLY INSIDE WINDOWS

